The paper discusses a probabilistic model for Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) implemented on neuromorphic hardware platforms, which falls under the intersection of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT). The focus on learning rules and training criteria suggests that cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI for the discussion of SNNs, and cs.SY and cs.IT for the graphical representation and statistical dependencies.
